Article policies

•  
[Neutral point of view](/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view) must be maintained, ensuring that all content is presented fairly and without bias, especially on politically sensitive topics such as drug policy.  

•  
[No original research](/Wikipedia:No_original_research) is permitted; all statements must be attributable to reliable published sources that are part of the public record.  

•  
[Verifiability](/Wikipedia:Verifiability) requires that every factual claim be supported by citations from reputable references, and unsourced or poorly sourced contentious material about living persons must be removed immediately.  

